President Cyril Ramaphosa visits the head office of the Department of Home Affairs in Tshwane to interact with Top Management and senior staff members. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa said the Home Affairs department must never be a home of corruption on Friday. He engaged with the department's senior officials at its head office in Pretoria, in an attempt to speed up the visa process. READ: SA passport holders can visit at least 100 countries without visas This is after the ANC NEC resolved to ease visa regulations to bolster tourism and the economy. "This was told to me by the President of China who said, improve your visas regime and security and many Chinese will come as tourists to South Africa and many other leaders have said the same thing," Ramaphosa said.